components.kdoc:
Aurum's pill — a compact, label-first status / token element. Renders Figma's
Pills component set (file `YvIxqu2oTlM6UnkL0OloHc`, node `5891-802`) across its
three `type`s and three states (default / `selected` → Figma "focus" / disabled),
with optional leading or trailing icons.

A pill is quieter than [AurumChip]: a chip is an action / filter CTA; a pill is a
status, category, or selectable token. Pass `onClick` to make it selectable (the
`selected` look — primary border + bold label — mirrors Figma's focus state).

@param label the pill text.
@param modifier applied to the pill root.
@param type the Figma `type` axis — see [AurumPillType].
@param selected the active look (Figma `state=focus`): primary border + bold label.
@param enabled when false renders the Figma `state=disabled` look and drops the click.
@param leadingIcon optional 16dp glyph before the label (Rectangular / Rounded only).
@param trailingIcon optional 16dp glyph after the label (Rectangular / Rounded only).
@param tag the uppercase ribbon text for [AurumPillType.WithTags]; ignored otherwise.
@param onClick optional — when set, the pill is clickable (role = Button).

