components.kdoc:
Aurum's circular progress spinner. A **scratch** component — drawn directly on
[Canvas] from `androidx.compose.foundation`, not derived from any Material 3 indicator.
Replaces the duplicated `CircularProgressLoader` found across 3+ modules. Renders Figma's
"Spinner" set (file `YvIxqu2oTlM6UnkL0OloHc`, node `4530-2084`): a full-circle track in
[trackColor] with a 90-degree arc in [color] rotating at constant speed, an optional
[label] (Figma `shownLabel`) placed [Right][AurumLoaderLabelPosition.Right] or
[Bottom][AurumLoaderLabelPosition.Bottom], and free [size] / [color] (the Figma `size`
and `color` axes are covered by these continuous params).

@param modifier the [Modifier] to apply to the root (the spinner, or the spinner+label row/column).
@param color the spinning arc colour — defaults to the primary interactive background token.
@param trackColor the background ring colour — defaults to the mid-contrast surface token.
@param strokeWidth the thickness of the ring — defaults to [Aurum.borderWidth.lg].
@param size the overall diameter — defaults to [Aurum.iconSize.xxl].
@param label optional text shown alongside the spinner (Figma `shownLabel`); null = spinner only.
@param labelPosition where the [label] sits relative to the spinner — see [AurumLoaderLabelPosition].

