components.kdoc:
Aurum's linear progress bar — a determinate 8dp track with a primary-fill
indicator. Renders Figma's "Progress Bar - Linear" set (file
`YvIxqu2oTlM6UnkL0OloHc`, node `5934-846`): an 8dp pill track
(`interactive.bgNeutralDefault`) with a primary indicator
(`interactive.bgPrimaryDefault`) sized to [progress]. Optionally shows a
header row (Figma `shownHeader`) with a leading [label] and the trailing
percentage (Figma `shownProgress`, via [showPercentage]).

Determinate only — for an indeterminate spinner use [AurumLoader].

@param progress the completed fraction, `0f..1f` (coerced).
@param modifier applied to the root column.
@param label optional header text shown above the bar (leading).
@param showPercentage when true, shows the rounded percentage in the header (trailing).

