components.kdoc:
Aurum's segmented progress bar — discrete progress across [total] segments, the first
[filled] of them complete. Renders Figma's "Progress Bar - Segmented" set (file
`YvIxqu2oTlM6UnkL0OloHc`, node `5889-2361`):

 - [AurumSegmentedProgressType.Bars] — [total] equal 8dp pill segments; the first
   [filled] are tinted by [intent], the rest `interactive.bgNeutralDefault`.
 - [AurumSegmentedProgressType.Bubbles] — the same, each segment capped by a 24dp
   numbered checkpoint (a stepper); completed steps fill + carry inverse-tinted numerals.

Optional header row (Figma `shownHeader`) with a leading [label] and the trailing
fraction percentage (Figma `shownProgress`, via [showPercentage]).

@param filled the number of completed segments, coerced to `0..total`.
@param total the segment count (coerced to at least 1).
@param modifier applied to the root column.
@param type bars or numbered bubbles — see [AurumSegmentedProgressType].
@param intent the filled colour family — see [AurumSegmentIntent].
@param label optional header text shown above the bar (leading).
@param showPercentage when true, shows the rounded `filled/total` percentage (trailing).

