components.kdoc:
Aurum's currency-prefixed numeric input. Delegates to [AurumTextField]
and adds a persistent currency leading slot plus an optional trailing
slot for a derived equivalent (e.g. gold grams). Formatting of [value]
is the caller's responsibility — pass a display-ready string.

@param value the current text value — already formatted for display
@param onValueChange called with the raw string the user typed (no automatic formatting)
@param modifier applied to the outer column
@param label optional label displayed above the field
@param helperText optional assistive text shown below the field
@param errorText when non-null, the field shows error styling and this replaces [helperText]
@param successText when non-null (and no error), the field shows success styling
@param currencySymbol the leading currency glyph — defaults to `"₹"`
@param suffixText optional trailing equivalent; hidden while [loading]
@param enabled whether the field accepts input
@param readOnly focusable but not editable; also forced read-only while [loading]
@param loading when `true`, the field is read-only and a small inline loader replaces [suffixText]

