components.kdoc:
Aurum's OTP (one-time password) input component.

Renders a row of underline-style digit cells that the user fills sequentially.
A single hidden [BasicTextField] captures keyboard input; the visible cells
are decorative columns (digit + coloured underline bar).

This is a **scratch** component — built entirely on
`androidx.compose.foundation` with zero `material3` imports.

@param value the current OTP string (digits only, length <= [length].count)
@param onValueChange callback invoked when the user types or deletes a digit
@param modifier the [Modifier] to apply to the outer column
@param length the number of digit cells — 4 or 6
@param label optional label text displayed above the cells
@param helperText optional helper/error/success text displayed below the cells
@param validationState controls underline and helper text colour
@param enabled whether the input accepts user interaction
@param onComplete optional callback invoked once all digits have been entered

