components.kdoc:
Aurum's root screen scaffold — the standard entry point for every
Aurum-powered screen.

Renders **edge-to-edge** by default. The top bar extends behind the
status bar; the bottom bar extends behind the navigation bar; the
content area is padded correctly via Scaffold's window insets.

## Usage

```kotlin
AurumScreen(
    topBar = {
        AurumPageHeader(
            title = "Settings",
            onBack = { navController.popBackStack() },
        )
    },
    isLoading = viewModel.isLoading,
) { padding ->
    SettingsContent(Modifier.padding(padding))
}
```

@param modifier applied to the root container
@param topBar top bar slot — typically [AurumPageHeader]. The top bar
  should apply `statusBarsPadding()` internally (AurumPageHeader does
  this when `applyStatusBarInsets = true`)
@param bottomBar bottom bar slot — typically a CTA button row. Should
  apply `navigationBarsPadding()` internally if it sits at the screen
  bottom edge.
@param snackbarHostState the [SnackbarHostState] for showing snackbars.
  Call `snackbarHostState.showSnackbar(...)` from a coroutine.
@param isLoading when true, draws a full-screen scrim (including behind
  system bars) with a centered [AurumLoader]
@param containerColor the screen background colour — defaults to the
  Aurum page base (white in light mode)
@param contentWindowInsets the window insets that the content should
  respect. Defaults to [ScaffoldDefaults.contentWindowInsets] which
  handles the remaining system insets not consumed by top/bottom bars.
@param content the screen content lambda. Receives [PaddingValues] that
  account for the top bar, bottom bar, and system insets. Apply via
  `Modifier.padding(it)`.

